302  friend istream &operator>>(istream &is, Math& math) {
303  char chr;
304  string lhs, rhs, oper;
305  while (is.get(chr)) {
306  if (Strings::isOperator(chr)) {
307  oper += chr;
308  } else if (!oper.empty()) {
309  rhs += chr;
310  } else {
311  lhs += chr;
312  }
313  }
314  math._lhs = Expr(lhs);
315  math._oper = oper;
316  if (Strings::isDigit(rhs)) {
317  math._rhs = Int(unstring<int>(rhs));
318  } else if (Strings::isNumber(rhs)) {
319  math._rhs = Real(unstring<double>(rhs));
320  } else {
321  math._rhs = Expr(rhs);
322  }
323  return is;
324  }

328  Expr::copy(other); // Let Base::copy() handle copying Base things
329  _lhs = other._lhs;
330  _rhs = other._rhs;
331  _oper = other._oper;
332  }

547  ostream &operator<<(ostream &os, const Math &math) {
548  string oper = math.oper();
549  if (oper.find('(') == string::npos) {
550  string lhs = stringify<Expr>(math.lhs());
551  // Wrap parens around sums to ensure proper precedence
552  if ((oper == "*" || oper == "/" || oper == "%") &&
553  (lhs.find('+') != string::npos || lhs.find('-') != string::npos)) {
554  lhs = "(" + lhs + ")";
555  }
556  os << lhs;
557  if (!math.rhs().empty()) {
558  string rhs = stringify<Expr>(math.rhs());
559  // Remove superfluous identity ops, e.g., *1 or +0.
560  if (!(oper == "*" && rhs == "1") && !(oper == "/" && rhs == "1") && !(oper == "%" && rhs == "1") &&
561  !(oper == "+" && rhs == "0") && !(oper == "-" && rhs == "0")) {
562  if (oper == "-" && rhs[0] == '-') {
563  oper = "+";
564  rhs = rhs.substr(1);
565  }
566  if (oper == "-" || !lhs.empty()) {
567  os << oper;
568  }
569  os << rhs;
570  }
571  }
572  } else {
573  os << oper;
574  if (!math.lhs().empty()) {
575  os << math.lhs() << ',';
576  }
577  os << math.rhs() << ')';
578  }
579  return os;
580  }

770  friend istream &operator>>(istream &is, Func &func) {
771  func._arity = 0;
772  is >> func._text;
773  bool inArgs = false;
774  string arg;
775  for (char chr : func._text) {
776  if (chr == '(' || chr == '[') {
777  inArgs = true;
778  } else if (chr == ')' || chr == ']') {
779  inArgs = false;
780  } else if (inArgs) {
781  if (chr == ',') {
782  func._arity += 1;
783  func._args.emplace_back(Expr(arg));
784  arg = "";
785  } else {
786  arg += chr;
787  }
788  } else {
789  func._name += chr;
790  }
791  }
792  if (!arg.empty()) {
793  func._arity += 1;
794  func._args.emplace_back(Expr(arg));
795  }
796  return is;
797  }

801  Expr::copy(other); // Let Base::copy() handle copying Base things
802  _name = other._name;

804  _args = other._args;
805  }

1172  void transClosure() {
1173  // Transitive Property Rules, forall a, b, c in |R:
1174  // a >= b ^ b >= c -> a >= c (1)
1175  // a <= b ^ b <= c -> a <= c (2)
1176  // If either is a strict inequality, then result is a strict inequality:
1177  // a >= b ^ b > c -> a > c (3)
1178  // a > b ^ b >= c -> a > c (4)
1179  // a <= b ^ b < c -> a < c (5)
1180  // a < b ^ b <= c -> a < c (6)
1181  // a = b -> a >= b:
1182  // a = b ^ b > c -> a > c (7)
1183  // a > b ^ b = c -> a > c (8)
1184  // a = b -> a <= b:
1185  // a = b ^ b < c -> a < c (9)
1186  // a < b ^ b = c -> a < c (10)
1187  //if (!Strings::isDigit(_upper.rhs().text())) {
1188  if (!(_lower.lhs().is_number() && _upper.rhs().is_number())) {
1189  _trans = Constr(_lower.lhs(), _upper.rhs(), _upper.relop());
1190  }
1191  //}
1192  }
1193 
1194  Constr _lower;
1195  Constr _upper;
1196  Constr _trans; // Transitive property...
1197  };

1865  Constr high = _constraints[n+1];

1875  Math size() const {
1876  Math expr;
1877  unsigned inc = 2;
1878  for (unsigned n = 0; n + 1 < _constraints.size(); n += inc) {
1879  Constr low = _constraints[n];
1880  Constr high = _constraints[n+1];
1881  if (low.rhs().is_iter() && high.lhs().is_iter()) {
1882  Expr lower = low.lhs();
1883  Expr upper = high.rhs();
1884 
1885  Math diff = (upper - lower);
1886  if (high.relop().find('=') != string::npos) {
1887  diff = diff + Int(1);
1888  }
1889 
1890  Math rhs = paren(diff);
1891  if (expr.empty()) {
1892  expr = rhs;
1893  } else {
1894  expr = expr * rhs;
1895  }
1896  inc = 2;
1897  } else {
1898  inc = 1;
1899  }
1900  }
1901  return expr;
1902  }

1924  friend istream &operator>>(istream &is, Space &space) {
1925  string token;
1926  is >> token;
1927  space.name(token);
1928  bool inIter = false;
1929  bool inConstr = false;
1930  string constr;
1931  while (is >> token) {
1932  if (!inIter && token[0] == '[') {
1933  inIter = true;
1934  token = token.substr(1);
1935  } else if (!inConstr && token == ":") {
1936  inConstr = true;
1937  }
1938  if (inIter) {
1939  if (token[token.size() - 1] == ']') {
1940  inIter = false;
1941  token = token.substr(0, token.size() - 1);
1942  } else {
1943  token = Strings::rtrim(token, ',');
1944  }
1945  vector<string> iters = Strings::split(token, ',');
1946  for (const string &iter : iters) {
1947  space.add(Iter(iter));
1948  }
1949  } else if (inConstr) {
1950  if (token == "&&" || token == "and") {
1951  // TODO: Come back to this...
1952  //space.add(Constr(constr));
1953  }
1954  constr += token + ' ';
1955  }
1956  cerr << token << " ";
1957  int stop = 1;
1958  }
1959  return is;
1960  }

2168  ExprTuple tupleMath(const ExprTuple& lhs, const ExprTuple& rhs, const char oper) {
2169  unsigned minLen, maxLen;
2170  if (lhs.size() > rhs.size()) {
2171  maxLen = lhs.size();
2172  minLen = rhs.size();
2173  } else {
2174  maxLen = rhs.size();
2175  minLen = lhs.size();
2176  }
2177 
2178  ExprTuple res(maxLen, Int(0));
2179  for (unsigned i = 0; i < minLen; i++) {
2180  if (oper == '+') {
2181  res[i] = lhs[i] + rhs[i];
2182  } else if (oper == '-') {
2183  string lexpr = lhs[i].text();
2184  string rexpr = rhs[i].text();
2185  size_t pos = lexpr.find(rexpr);
2186  if (pos != string::npos) {
2187  lexpr.erase(pos, rexpr.size());
2188  if (lexpr.empty()) {
2189  res[i] = Int(0);
2190  } else {
2191  res[i] = lhs[i];
2192  res[i].text(lexpr);

3369  vector<int> calcReuseDist(const vector<Access>& accs) {
3370  vector<int> rdist(accs[0].tuple().size(), 0);
3371  for (const auto& acc : accs) {
3372  vector<Expr> tuple = acc.tuple();
3373  for (unsigned i = 0; i < tuple.size(); i++) {
3374  string num = Strings::number(tuple[i].text());
3375  int dist = num.empty() ? 0 : unstring<int>(num);
3376  dist -= rdist[i];
3377  rdist[i] = dist;
3378  }
3379  }
3380  for (unsigned i = 0; i < rdist.size(); i++) {
3381  if (rdist[i] < 0) {
3382  rdist[i] = -rdist[i];
3383  }
3384  rdist[i] += 1;
3385  }
3386  return rdist;

3461  void addComp(Comp& comp) {

3467  bool compExists = _flowGraph->contains(compName);
3468  if (compExists) {
3469  compNode = (CompNode *) _flowGraph->get(compName);

3471  } else {

3473  compNode->attr("flops", to_string(_nflops));

3476

3478  vector<Expr> domExprs;
3479  for (Constr& constr : comp.space().constraints()) {
3480  domExprs.push_back(constr.lhs());
3481  domExprs.push_back(constr.rhs());
3482  }
3483 
3484  // 2) Add integer data nodes for UFs + SCs
3485  for (Expr& expr : domExprs) {
3486  if (expr.is_func()) {
3487  Expr* size = getSize(comp, Func(expr));
3488  if (_flowGraph->contains(expr.text())) {
3489  dataNode = (DataNode*) _flowGraph->get(expr.text());
3490  dataNode->size(size);
3491  } else {
3492  // Make integer typed data node and add incoming edge to stmt node.
3493  dataNode = (DataNode*) _flowGraph->add(new DataNode(&expr, expr.text(), size, _indexType));
3494  cerr << "Added read node '" << dataNode->label() << "'" << endl;
3495  }

3502  vector<Expr> writeExprs;
3503  for (Math& stmt : comp.statements()) {

3505  if (stmt.oper().find('=') != string::npos) {
3506  // If operator has an equal sign, it is an assignment, so the LHS is an output node.
3507  writeExprs.push_back(stmt.lhs());

3537  break;

3539  }

3564  string rhs = line.substr(pos + 1);
3565  for (const auto &sit : _spaces) {
3566  if (marked.find(sit.first) == marked.end()) {
3567  if (Strings::in(lhs, sit.first, true)) {
3568  writeExprs.push_back(sit.second);
3569  marked[sit.first] = true;
3570  } else if (Strings::in(rhs, sit.first, true)) {
3571  readExprs.push_back(sit.second);
3572  marked[sit.first] = true;
3573  }
3574  }
3575  }
3576  }
3577  }
3578  } else if (!stmt.rhs().is_scalar()) {
3579  readExprs.push_back(stmt.rhs());
3580  }
3581  }
3582 
3583  for (Constr& constr : comp.guards()) {
3584  string guard = constr.text();
3585  if (!guard.empty()) {
3586  for (const auto &sit : _spaces) {
3587  if (Strings::in(guard, sit.first, true)) {
3588  readExprs.push_back(sit.second);
3589  }
3590  }
3591  }
3592  }
3593 
3594  // 4) Create read nodes.
3595  for (Expr& expr : readExprs) {
3596  Func func = Func(expr);
3597  Expr* size = getSize(comp, func);
3598  string type = getType(comp, func);
3599  if (_flowGraph->contains(expr.text())) {
3600  dataNode = (DataNode*) _flowGraph->get(expr.text());
3601  dataNode->size(size);
3602  } else {
3603  // Create data node from Access object, and add incoming edge edge to statement node.
3604  dataNode = (DataNode*) _flowGraph->add(new DataNode(&expr, expr.text(), size, type));
3605  cerr << "GraphMaker: Added read node '" << dataNode->label() << "'" << endl;
3606  }
3607 
3608  cerr << "GraphMaker: '" << dataNode->label() << "' -> '" << compNode->label() << "'\n";
3609  _flowGraph->add(dataNode, compNode);
3610 
3611  string space = dataNode->label();
3612  auto itr = _accessMap.find(space);
3613  if (itr != _accessMap.end()) {
3614  for (const auto& access : itr->second) {
3615  //cerr << "Adding read access '" << access << "'" << endl;
3616  compNode->add_read(access);
3617  }
3618  } else {
3619  Access access(space, {Int(0)});
3620  compNode->add_read(access);
3621  }
3622  }
3623 
3624  if (!compExists) {
3625  _flowGraph->add(compNode);
3626  cerr << "GraphMaker: Added comp node '" << compNode->label() << "'" << endl;
3627  }
3628 
3629  for (Expr& expr : writeExprs) {
3630  Func func = Func(expr);
3631  Expr* size = getSize(comp, func);
3632  string type = getType(comp, func);
3633  if (_flowGraph->contains(expr.text())) {
3634  dataNode = (DataNode*) _flowGraph->get(expr.text());
3635  dataNode->size(size);
3636  } else {
3637  // Create data node from Access object, and add outgoing edge edge to statement node.
3638  // Mark output node as persistent (immutable) or temporary (optimizable) -- how to tell?
3639  dataNode = (DataNode*) _flowGraph->add(new DataNode(&expr, expr.text(), size, type));
3640  cerr << "GraphMaker: Added write node '" << dataNode->label() << "'" << endl;
3641  }
3642  if (!_flowGraph->contains(dataNode, compNode) || _flowGraph->ignoreCycles()) {
3643  _flowGraph->add(compNode, dataNode);
3644  cerr << "GraphMaker: '" << compNode->label() << "' -> '" << dataNode->label() << "'\n";
3645  } else { //if (!_flowGraph->ignoreCycles()) {
3646  // Cycle! => create hierarchical node
3647  _flowGraph->remove(compNode);
3648  cerr << "GraphMaker: Removed comp node '" << compNode->label() << "' to prevent cycle" << endl;
3649  makeHierarchical((CompNode*) compNode, (DataNode*) dataNode);
3650  }
3651 
3652  string space = dataNode->label();
3653  auto itr = _accessMap.find(space);
3654  if (itr != _accessMap.end()) {
3655  for (const auto& access : itr->second) {
3656  //cerr << "Adding write access '" << access << "'" << endl;
3657  compNode->add_write(access);
3658  }
3659  } else {
3660  Access access(space, {Int(0)});
3661  compNode->add_write(access);
3662  }
3663  }
3664 
3665  _accessMap.clear(); // Clear accesses for next computation.
3666  clearFLOPs(); // Reset FLOPs.
3667  }
3668 
3669  bool mergeComps(const string& name, Space& lspace, Space& rspace, const string& oper) {
3670  bool merged = false;
3671 
3672  // 1st condition: lspace has a producer in this graph...
3673  DataNode* data = (DataNode*) _flowGraph->get(lspace.name());
3674  vector<Edge*> ins = _flowGraph->in_edges(data);
3675  if (ins.size() > 0) {
3676  CompNode* prod = (CompNode*) ins[0]->source();
3677  Comp* comp = prod->comp();
3678 
3679  // 2nd condition: computation only has one statement.
3680 
3681  // 3rd condition: producer is not a forall...
3682 
3683  if (comp->statements().size() > 0) {
3684  Math stmt = comp->statements()[0];
3685 
3686  // Create an access for right hand side.
3687  Access readAcc(rspace.name(), rspace.iterators());
3688  Math expr(paren(stmt.rhs()), readAcc, oper.substr(0,1));
3689  Math new_stmt(stmt.lhs(), expr, stmt.oper());
3690  comp->statement(0, new_stmt);
3691 
3692  // Now the hard part, update the graph, and re-invoke addComp
3693  //_flowGraph->remove(prod);
3694  incFLOPs();
3695  addComp(*comp);
3696  merged = true;
3697  }
3698  }
3699 
3700  return merged;
3701  }

3827  string codegen(const string& path = "", const string& name = "",
3828  const string& lang = "C", const string& ompsched = "") {

3832  cpath += ".c";
3833  } else if (isobj) {
3834  cpath = Strings::replace(cpath, ".o", ".c");
3835  }

3837  reschedule(name); // Run scheduling pass if needed.
3838  //data_reduce(name); // Run data redux pass if needed.

3843  cgen = new CudaGenVisitor(path);
3844  } else if (!_flowGraph->attr("parallelized").empty()) {
3845  cgen = new OmpGenVisitor(path, lang);

3848  cgen->ompSchedule(ompsched);

3852  cgen->defineFlags(_defines);

3854 
3855  for (const auto& iter : _consts) {

3861 
3862  if (name.empty()) {
3863  _flowGraph->indexType(_indexType);
3864  cgen->walk(_flowGraph);
3865  } else {
3866  _graphs[name]->indexType(_indexType);
3867  cgen->walk(_graphs[name]);
3868  }
3869 
3870  if (isobj) {
3871  compile(cpath, path);
3872  }
3873 
3874  string code = cgen->str();
3875  delete cgen;
3876 
3877  return code;
3878  }

3991  Expr* getSize(const Comp& comp, const Func& func) {
3992  Expr* expr = nullptr;
3993  Math math;
3994  auto iter = _spaces.find(func.name());
3995  if (iter != _spaces.end()) {
3996  Space space = iter->second;
3997  if (!space.constraints().empty()) {
3998  expr = new Math(space.size());
3999  }
4000  } else if (func.arity() > 0) {
4001  expr = new Math(getFuncSize(comp, func));
4002  }
4003  if (expr == nullptr) {
4004  expr = new Int(1); // Assume scalar
4005  }

4009  Math getFuncSize(const Comp& comp, const Func& func) {
4010  Math math;
4011  for (Expr& arg : func.args()) {
4012  string argtxt = arg.text();
4013  auto mapkey = _iters.find(argtxt);
4014  bool isIter = (mapkey != _iters.end());
4015  if (!isIter && hasIter(argtxt)) {
4016  istringstream is(argtxt);
4017  is >> math;
4018  argtxt = math.lhs().text();
4019  mapkey = _iters.find(argtxt);
4020  isIter = (mapkey != _iters.end());
4021  }
4022 
4023  if (isIter) {
4024  Iter iter = mapkey->second;
4025  vector<Constr> constraints = comp.space().constraints(argtxt);
4026  Expr lower, upper;
4027  string oplow, opup;
4028  for (const Constr& constr : constraints) {
4029  if (constr.lhs().text() == iter.name()) {
4030  upper = constr.rhs();
4031  opup = constr.relop();
4032  } else if (constr.rhs().text() == iter.name()) {
4033  lower = constr.lhs();
4034  oplow = constr.relop();
4035  }
4036  }
4037 
4038  Math diff = (upper - lower);
4039  if (opup == "<=") {
4040  diff = Math(diff, Int(1), "+");
4041  }
4042  if (oplow == "<") {
4043  diff = Math(diff, Int(1), "-");
4044  }
4045  diff = paren(diff); //Math(NullExpr, diff, "(");
4046 
4047  if (argtxt == math.lhs().text()) {
4048  math = Math(diff, math.rhs(), math.oper());
4049  } else if (!math.oper().empty()) {
4050  math = math * diff;
4051  } else {
4052  math = diff;
4053  }
4054  } else if (_consts.find(argtxt) != _consts.end()) {
4055  math = Math(_consts[argtxt], Int(0), "+");
4056  }
4057  }
4058 
4059  return math;
4060  }

4062  string getType(const Comp& comp, const Func& func) const {
4063  // Assume symbolic constants and uninterpreted functions have index type...
4064  if (func.is_func() || _consts.find(func.name()) != _consts.end()) {
4065  return _indexType;
4066  } else {
4067  for (const Math& stmt : comp.statements()) {
4068  // Assignment to a symbolic constant or iter, or vice versa...
4069  if ((stmt.rhs().text().rfind(func.name(), 0) == 0 &&
4070  (_consts.find(stmt.lhs().text()) != _consts.end() ||
4071  _iters.find(stmt.lhs().text()) != _iters.end())) ||
4072  (stmt.lhs().text().rfind(func.name(), 0) == 0 &&
4073  (_consts.find(stmt.rhs().text()) != _consts.end() ||
4074  _iters.find(stmt.rhs().text()) != _iters.end()))) {
4075  return _indexType;
4076  }
4077  }
4078  }
4079  return _dataType;
4080  }
